result.execSummary:
The defendant Jesse N Robinson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Substantial Battery-Intend Bodily Harm [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(2).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Jesse N Robinson in court with attorney Mary D Scholle.  Defendant Jesse N Robinson in custody.  Nicolas J Heitman appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing hearing proceed.  Statements made by State, defense and defendant.  Additional statements by Crystal R. and Nikki R.  The court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM term in the Wisconsin State Prison of 3 YEARS with credit for 77 days time served, the term of INITIAL CONFINEMENT is 18 MONTHS, the term of EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 18 MONTHS. Court ordered sentence stayed and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 3 YEARS.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION/EXTENDED SUPERVISION
-Serve 60 days in the House of Correction as Condition Time, STAYED pending review; if requested.
-Batterers Intervention program, or a course in anger management.
-Parenting classes.
-Mental health evaluation, take all prescribed medications.
-AODA assessment, comply with recommended treatment.
-Absolute sobriety, random urine screens.
-Treatment and/or counseling as determined by agent.
-No contact with victim. 
-Obtain/maintain employment.
-Obtain GED/HSED.
-No contact with firearms.
-Serve 180 days in the House of Correction as Condition Time; no release privileges.
-Pay all court costs, fees, and surcharges including: supervision fees, and DNA, DV, and Victim/Witness surcharges to be paid from 25% of prison funds, balance paid during Extended Supervision if revoked, otherwise due during probation period, failure to pay results in a civil judgment.
-Provide DNA Sample.

*Court finds defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program OR the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.
*Court advised defendant of right to seek post conviction relief. 
*Court advised defendant of penalties for violation of NO CONTACT ORDER. 
*Court advised due to DV conviction under federal law the defendant is prohibited from firearm possession.
*Court advised due to felony conviction the defendant is prohibited from firearm possession, and defendant's voting rights are suspended and may not vote until civil rights are restored.
